'''Anandadhara''' is a fortnightly entertainment magazine in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite news|title=Juton Chowdhury no more|url=https://observerbd.com/details.php?id=123145|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=The Daily Observer|publisher=observerbd.com|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Suborna ties the knot again|url=https://bdnews24.com/entertainment/2008/07/07/suborna-ties-the-knot-again|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=bdnews24.com}}</ref> The magazine is published by [[Mahfuz Anam]], who is also the editor of [[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|The Daily Star]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Shaptahik 2000, Anandadhara celebrate 12th anniversary|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/cache/cached-news-details-139459.html|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=archive.thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|language=en}}</ref>
==History== Anandadhara was founded in May 1998 as a film industry magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anandadhara and 2000 celebrate 13th anniversary|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-185675|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=15 May 2011|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Raju|first1=Zakir Hossain|title=Bangladesh Cinema and National Identity: In Search of the Modern?|date=2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317601814|page=18|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XXDfBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA18&lpg=PA18&dq=anandadhara+magazine&source=bl&ots=Be8y2gxD4c&sig=a38UoOV97mUdNhLt0s1UaZVW1uE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjp-N_gpeHZAhUR0FMKHVxdB7IQ6AEIfTAT#v=onepage&q=anandadhara%20magazine&f=false|accessdate=10 March 2018|language=en}}</ref> [[Shahadat Chowdhury]], editor of [[Bichitra]], was the founding editor of Anandadhara.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chowdhury|first1=Esha|title=Freedom from life|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/magazine/2010/12/01/remembrance.htm|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=www.thedailystar.net|publisher=Star Weekend Magazine}}</ref> The magazine started the Lux Anandadhara Miss Bangladesh Photogenic which is the forerunner to the [[Lux Channel i Superstar]].<ref>{{cite news|title=SHANKHACHIL - BONDING THE BENGALS|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/cover-story/shankhachil-bonding-the-bengals-1206490|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=9 April 2016|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Beauty pageant|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2003/09/12/d30912140372.htm|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=archive.thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star}}</ref> In June 2011, the magazine editor [[Arun Chowdhury]] was replaced by [[Moinul Ahsan Saber]] the editor of [[Shaptahik 2000]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Arun not with Anandadhara anymore|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-194792|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=19 July 2011|language=en}}</ref>
