{{Infobox music festival | name = Yaga Gathering | image = Yaga gathering.jpg | alt = Festival attendees stand silhouetted against a multicoloured laser-light show | caption = Yaga Gathering 2013 | genre = [[Psychedelic trance]], [[chill-out music]], [[ambient dub]], [[dub techno]] | dates = July/August | location = Spengla Lake, [[Varėna District Municipality|Varėna]], [[Lithuania]] | coordinates = {{coord|54|20|14.80|N|24|46|31.60|E|type:event|display=inline,title}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://yaga.lt/how-to-get-there/#MAP |title=Location: How to Get There § Maps |website=Yaga.lt |access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref> | years_active = 2003–present | founders = | attendance = | capacity = | website = {{URL|http://yaga.lt/}} }}
'''Yaga Gathering''' is a [[transformational festival]] hosted in a clearing in Ežeraitis Forest, at the edge of Spengla Lake in the [[Varėna District Municipality|Varėna District]] of southern [[Lithuania]].<ref name="RA">{{cite web|url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/events/1108616 |title=Yaga Gathering 2018: Shapeshifting |website=[[Resident Advisor]] |access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.last.fm/festival/4323368 |title=Yaga Gathering 2017 |website=[[Last.fm]] |access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> The festival has no corporate sponsors,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bhindthelyrics.com/2016/07/05/10-reasons-why-you-have-to-experience-yaga-gathering-2016/ |title=10 reasons why you have to experience Yaga Gathering 2016 |last=Lenktyte |first=Deimante |date=5 July 2016 |access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref><ref name="Harold">{{cite web |url=http://musicexportfund.com/send-helicopters-yaga-festival-2015-review/ |title='Send helicopters': Yaga Festival 2015 review |last=Harold |first=Mark Adam |date=21 September 2015 |access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> and is financed by ticket sales. The site of the festival is about {{convert|60|km}} south of [[Vilnius]], the capital of Lithuania.<ref name="Harold"/>
[[DJ]]s and live bands from various countries perform on five stages: the Main Stage, the Forest Stage, the Concept Stage, the Chillout Stage and the Silent Stage. Classes and activities are mong the festival's other attractions, including [[yoga]] sessions, [[handicraft]] workshops, and a children's area. The design of the event space incorporates [[art installation]]s and [[Art exhibit|exhibits]]. Most of the festival infrastructure is built using [[biodegradable]] materials.{{citation needed|date=July 2017}} Attendees are permitted to [[Camping|camp]] on-site.
==History== [[File:Shambala festival 2003 (Lithuania) flyer.jpg|thumb|left|A [[Flyer (pamphlet)|flyer]] for Shambala Festival 2003]]
Yaga Gathering was originally a [[psychedelic trance]] [[music festival]] called '''Shambala Festival'''—named for the mythical hidden kingdom of [[Shambhala]]. The first event took place from 18–20 July 2003; it was small and not widely advertised. Organisers produced a second festival in 2005, and by the third festival in 2006 they had added a yoga class, a drum circle, film screenings, lectures, and a [[sweat lodge]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://yaga.lt/history/2006/ |title=History: 2006 |website=Yaga.lt |access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref>
The 2007 festival was renamed Yaga Gathering. Yaga Gathering returned in 2009,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://psytraveller.net/lithuania/ |title=Psychedelic Flash in Lithuania |last=Shoom |first=Anton |date=28 May 2013 |origyear=2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150603003233/http://psytraveller.net/lithuania/ |archive-date=3 June 2015 |website=Psytraveller.net |access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> and again in 2011 through 2017. There was no Yaga Festival in 2008 or 2010. Yaga Gathering 2017 took place on 3–7 August 2017; the 13th festival, Yaga Gathering 2018, is planned for 9–13 August 2018.<ref name="RA"/>
In [[Vedic]] tradition, a ''yaga'' ({{lang-sa|याग|translit=[[yajna]]|lit=sacrifice|link=no}})<ref>{{cite web |url=http://spokensanskrit.de/index.php?tinput=yAga |title=याग |website=Spoken Sanskrit Dictionary |access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> is a ritual performed in front of a sacred fire, or one in which an offering is burned in a fire. The festival's name alludes to spiritual rebirth. {{-}}
